It is all sounds good. But....

Sometimes, writing complicated math. classes, it is important to distinguish
sign of zero. +0.0 and -0.0 are different a bit, for example they cause
different sign of infinity at f(x)=1.0/x ... it may have sense to have
method that will compare doubles including this neat place.

for example max(-0.0,+0.0) should return +0.0 if I test my own realizaton of
max I will want to distinguish them :) it is not possible with &quot;delta&quot; :)
more over it is not possible with &quot;==&quot; because (+0.0)==(-0.0), sign of zero
play role only in / and some functions in java.lang.Math

I prefer there was special assert for that situations

